# Web3Forms access key — get a free one at https://web3forms.com
# Enter your email (shaannkkyy2403@gmail.com) there and they email you this key.
#
# NOTE: This key is PUBLIC by design. It only authorizes "send a form to the
# inbox tied to this key." It is safe to ship in client-side code. Keeping it
# in .env is for convenience/hygiene (easy to swap, not committed), NOT secrecy.
#
# Copy this file to ".env" and fill in your key. Vite only exposes vars
# prefixed with VITE_ to the browser.
VITE_WEB3FORMS_KEY=your-access-key-here
